text.tspan: Spoken through men by Spirit borne—
The coming Savior of God’s plan;
God’s promises made real through faith,
Laid hold of by my prayer.
My spirit with His Spirit joined,
Mingled with prayer, becomes in me
Cry out at dawn, and hope in them,
As hart doth pant for cooling streams,
I pant, O God, for Thee.
Do make my heart, good ground!
Let Thy word’s seed take root and grow,
Man shall not live by bread alone,
But by Thy word each day.
Reaching me in my lowest state,
To be my all in all.
Thy lips bring words of grace;
Sweeter than honey to my mouth,
I ate the words I found,
And they became the gladness, joy,
As guileless milk, then solid food—
Which divides spirit from the soul,
It is God-breathed to make complete
The man of God in me.
From sin released, to land returned—
Which each day fresh does fall,
To be our all in all.
Save from fall’s sin and stain;
Hold forth the word of life;
With it, go forth to sow,
That God may cause to grow.
With one another, Christ we share,
Speak, teach, admonish, sing with grace
To saints and God as well.
As Son of Man midst lampstands moves,
We’re by its washing, cleansing pow’r
Though heav’n and earth shall pass away,
